from collections import defaultdict

def find_minimum_M(A, N):
    L = [[]]
    D = defaultdict(int)
    S = set()
    p = 1
    for n in A:
        if n in S:
            q = D[n]
        else:
            S.add(n)
            q = len(L)
            L.append([])
            D[n] = q
        L[q].append(p)
        p += 1
    SL = list(S)
    SL.sort()
    p = 0
    M = 1
    for n in SL:
        q = D[n]
        if len(L[q]) == 1:
            z = L[q][0]
            if z < p:
                M += 1
            p = z
        else:
            v = L[q][-1]
            if v > p:
                k = 0
                while L[q][k] < p:
                    k += 1
                p = L[q][k]
            else:
                M += 1
                p = L[q][0]
    return M
